Explore Continuing Education





Fitness Nutrition Specialist Program (2.5 CECs)
Gain the expertise to provide practical, relevant nutrition advice to your clients while staying within your scope of practice.
Learn More »





Behavior Change Specialist Program (2.5 CECs)
Develop the practical, hands-on skills needed to guide people toward behavior change in one-on-one, group and virtual settings.
Learn More »









Movement-Based Exercise Workshop (0.8 CECs)
Live Dates/Locations: Las Vegas, NV (9/16/2017), Dallas, TX (9/23/2017), Falmouth, VA (9/24/2017), San Antonio, TX (9/24/2017), Healdsburg, CA (10/14/2017) 
Register Now »







Free Continuing Education Webinars (0.1 CECs)
Watch our ACE experts discuss exercise theory, business strategy and a host of other topics for FREE now, and pay for the continuing education quiz later.
Learn More »





THE BIOMECHANICS METHOD CORRECTIVE EXERCISE SPECIALIST (8.0 CECs)
Develop skills in assessment, anatomy, corrective exercise and program design to help clients plagued by muscle and joint pain.
Learn More »







Pilates Mat Training (0.4 CECs)
Learn the six traditional Pilates principles and how they combine to form the basis of all Pilates movements.
Learn More »





Program Design and Implementation Strategies for Weight Loss (0.4 CECs)
When clients have lived most of their life either overweight or on an unhealthy track, the same strategies you use to design exercise programs for other clients may not apply. 
Learn More »










































