Back|ACEFitness Certifications ACE Certification Exams










NCCA-Accredited Certifications

Personal Trainer
Get certified to lead one-on-one or small-group training sessions.


Group Fitness Instructor
Empower yourself to design and lead all formats with confidence and expertise.


Health Coach
Gain versatile expertise in behavior change, fitness and nutrition.


Medical Exercise Specialist
Work alongside healthcare teams and lead clients with multiple health issues.






STAY INFORMED WITH ACE
Sign up to receive relevant, science-based health and fitness news from ACE each month.









Specialist Programs

Behavior Change
Develop hands-on, practical skills to facilitate long-term behavior change.


Fitness Nutrition
Provide practical, relevant nutrition advice within your scope of practice.


Sports Conditioning
Help athletes effectively improve balance, strength, agility and speed.


Weight Management
Guide clients affected by overweight and obesity to sustainable change.


Senior Fitness
Prevent muscle deterioration and boost quality of life for older adults.


Orthopedic Exercise
Restore movement and boost function in clients following orthopedic rehab.


Youth Fitness
Build age-appropriate fitness programs and instill the value of health.


Functional Training
Help all clients move more efficiently, prevent injury and build strength.


Mind Body
Improve mindfulness by learning to incorporate yoga and Pilates.


Therapeutic Exercise
Use exercise to address metabolic diseases and musculoskeletal disorders.






Military Support
Explore news about discounts and special ACE programs for military.


Peer Fitness Trainer Certification
Explore our unique certification created specifically for firefighters.


Corrective Exercise Specialist
Learn to alleviate musculoskeletal pain using The Biomechanics Method.




Certification Verification
Find ACE Certified professionals near you or verify that a pro you’re considering working with holds an ACE Certification.








Register for Your ACE Exam
Computer-based testing sites are found in hundreds of cities worldwide. For more information on what to expect on your exam, check out the ACE Certification Candidate Handbook.


Take a Computer-Based Exam


Find An Exam Location

                        Computer-based exams are the most popular format due to convenience and the vast number of locations that offer them. The electronic format also allows you to receive your results instantly.
                    

Must be at least 18 years old
Must hold a current, government-issued photo I.D.
Must meet the eligibility requirements to sit for desired exam as stated in the ACE Certification Candidate Handbook
Must hold a CPR/AED certification at time of registration that will still be valid on exam date. Course must include a live skills check. Online-only CPR/AED not accepted.
Must register at least 10 days prior to exam
May register either online (preferred) or by Mail

First-time exam only pricing is $249 for Group Fitness Instructor exam, $399 for Personal Trainer and Health Coach exams, and $499 for Medical Exercise Specialist exam



For more details on the cost of our exams, eligibility requirements, rescheduling, our cancellation policy, retakes and special accommodations, check out our FAQs.




























